					<br /><b>Joined:</b> Tue Apr 11, 2006 4:08 am<br /><b>Posts:</b> 140<br /><b>Location:</b> PL
				</span>

			</td>
			<td valign="top">
				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">Is it possible to make a copy of WRAM (copy of 1024/960 byte) to VRAM memory? Something like the &quot;shadow OAM&quot; (256 byte page 2 copied to OAM in NMI time), but &quot;SHADOW NT&quot; - 1024 byte (or 960 byte withhout ATTR table) $0400-07FF WRAM to VRAM $2000 ?<br /><br />I know it's a waste of memory, but if it is possible and that the NMI is enough time to copy the amount of memory?</div>

					
						<div class="postbody"><br />_________________<br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://forum.emunes.pl/">http://forum.emunes.pl/</a><!-- m --></div>
